summary_markdown: This data presents a chronological evolution of the visual representation of Betty Crocker, a brand icon, through a series of portraits spanning from 1936 to 1996. Each portrait is associated with a specific year, illustrating changes in her depicted appearance over six decades. The progression shows a shift in hairstyle, facial features, and overall style, reflecting evolving aesthetic trends and brand identity. This visual timeline demonstrates a comparative approach, highlighting the distinct iterations of the Betty Crocker persona at different points in time, rather than depicting a process or hierarchical structure. The consistent use of a portrait format across all years underscores the enduring nature of this iconic figure while simultaneously showcasing her adaptation to contemporary visual standards.
